-- Beckham Tops Sports List With 19% Wealth Gain, Sunday Times Says
-- B y   T h o m a s   B i e s h e u v e l
-- 2012-05-06T10:44:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-06/beckham-tops-sports-list-with-19-wealth-gain-sunday-times-says.html
Britain and Ireland’s 100 richest
sportsmen increased their fortunes a collective 8.9 percent in
the past 12 months to 3 billion pounds ($4.9 billion), the
Sunday Times said.  David Beckham , former captain of England’s national soccer
team, advanced to the top of the newspaper’s annual Sports  Rich
List  from No. 2 last year after he boosted his wealth by 25
million pounds, or 19 percent.  People involved in soccer accounted for 48 of the top 100,
with a combined wealth of 1.22 billion pounds, while golf and
motor sports accounted for 12 each, the Sunday Times reported.
There were no women on the list, the top 10 of whom are listed
below:  1. David Beckham, soccer (160 million pounds)
2. Paul Caddick and family, rugby union (150 million pounds)
3. Dave Whelan and family, soccer (140 million pounds)
4. Tony O’Reilly, rugby union (120 million pounds)
5. Johnny Dumfries, motor racing (110 million pounds)
6. Lennox Lewis, boxing (95 million pounds)
7. Eddie  Irvine , motor racing (80 million pounds)
8. Jody Scheckter, motor racing (60 million pounds)
9.  Lewis Hamilton , motor racing (55 million pounds)
10. Jenson Button, motor racing (53 million pounds)  To contact the reporter on this story:
